<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="447" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">561.333D3/14: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Secretary General of the Third Pan American Coffee
                                Conference</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Aguilar</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-17">June 17, 1940</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In response to your letter of June 14, 1940, the Department of State has
                            designated Mr. Paul C. Daniels, Foreign Service Officer, to attend the
                            Third Pan-American Coffee Conference as its observer.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>